member.remarks:
Setting this property to a string that contains one or more style rules applies the style rules to the document. For example, you can set it to
body { font-size: 20px; }
to change the document's default font size to 20px.

item.description:
By default, the built-in spellchecker uses the system language. You can override the language using this command line argument. Multiple languages can be separated by ",". For example, the following code enables spellchecking on English (U.S.) and Spanish (Spain):
EO.WebEngine.Engine.Default.Options.ExtraCommandLineArgs = "--override-spell-check-lang=en-US,es-ES";
EO.WebEngine.Engine.Default.Options.ExtraCommandLineArgs = "--override-spell-check-lang=en-US,es-ES"
